The LFL, maximum closed vessel deflagration pressure (
P
m a x
), and laminar burning velocity (
S
L
) of each synthetic gas mixture were then measured experimentally using the same methodology as Barowy et al. [34]. The LFL was determined by testing conducted in a 20L spherical pressure vessel per ASTM E918 [35]. The maximum closed vessel deflagration pressure (
P
m a x
) was determined experimentally in the aforementioned 20L pressure sphere following EN 15967 [36]. The laminar burning velocity was determined experimentally using the vertical tube method following ISO 817 [37]. The specifications and procedures for these tests are discussed in detail in [34] with results in Section 4.1.
